        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47336",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rodp82",
                        "name": "rodp82",
                        "displayName": "Rod Pattison",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem here was being caused by the while-statement on line 472 of Zend_Tool_Framework_Client_Console_ArgumentParser class\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nwhile (($wordOnTop = array_shift($this->_argumentsWorking))){\r\n    \/\/...\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nThere was the possibility of $wordOnTop being == 0 which would break out the while loop\r\ni.e zf create action actionName 0 moduleName\r\n\r\nJust change to seems to fix things\r\n{code}\r\nwhile (($wordOnTop = array_shift($this->_argumentsWorking)) !== false){\r\n    \/\/...\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI've attached a patch",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rodp82",
                        "name": "rodp82",
                        "displayName": "Rod Pattison",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-07-01T06:40:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-07-01T06:40:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50314",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello, this issue persists with ZF 1.11.11.\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-17T18:52:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-17T18:52:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50315",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I made several tests with Rod fix. You have also to update Action.php Otherwise you will have a fatal error.\r\n\r\n# This patch file was generated by NetBeans IDE\r\n# It uses platform neutral UTF-8 encoding and \\n newlines.\r\n--- C:\\xampp\\zf\\library\\Zend\\Tool\\Project\\Provider\\Action.php\r\n+++ C:\\xampp\\htdocs\\Test\\library\\Zend\\Tool\\Project\\Provider\\Action.php\r\n@@ -221,6 +221,7 @@\r\n         }\r\n         $viewResource = Zend_Tool_Project_Provider_View::createResource($this->_loadedProfile, $name, $controllerName, $module);\r\n         if ($viewIncluded) {\r\n+            \r\n             if ($this->_registry->getRequest()->isPretend()) {\r\n                 $response->appendContent(\r\n                     'Would create a view script for the ' . $name . ' action method at ' . $viewResource->getContext()->getPath()\r\n\r\nWith both fixes it is working fine, but default value. That is you must specify 1 on the command line if you want the view to be generated.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-17T19:10:25.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-17T19:10:25.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50316",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Pay attention, these fixes cause the default value to be 0 = no action\/view\/etc. creation",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-17T19:27:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-17T19:27:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50334",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think I found the solution. In ArgumentParser.php, apply this fix:\r\n\r\n@@ -469,9 +469,7 @@\r\n         \r\n         \/\/ if non-option arguments exist, attempt to process them before processing options\r\n         $wordStack = array();\r\n-        while (count($this->_argumentsWorking)){\r\n-            $wordOnTop = array_shift($this->_argumentsWorking);           \r\n-\r\n+        while (($wordOnTop = array_shift($this->_argumentsWorking))) {\r\n             if (substr($wordOnTop, 0, 1) != '-') {\r\n                 array_push($wordStack, $wordOnTop);\r\n             } else {\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=eboniface",
                        "name": "eboniface",
                        "displayName": "Eric Boniface",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-19T09:59:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-19T09:59:23.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
